      • getAt

        public IFIXMessage getAt(int relativeIndex)
        Description copied from interface: FIXMessageStore
        Return the FIX message at the specified relative index. TODO This indexing mechanism is not quite right. Consider making 0 the current message, 1 the start of the list and so on.
        Specified by:
        getAt in interface FIXMessageStore
        Parameters:
        relativeIndex - Zero and positive indices are relative to messages from the start of the store. That is, an index of 0 implies the first message and index of 1 the second and so on up to the size of the list. A negative index is relative to the end of the list counting backwards. That is, an index of -1 refers to the next to last message, -2 the one before that and so on.
        Returns:
        The message at the specified relativeIndex if it is in range, null otherwise.
